# Multiple Linear Regression {#sec-multiple}

## Model Specification

We add **horsepower** (`hp`) and **number of cylinders** (`cyl`) as predictors.

$$
\text{mpg}_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1\,\text{wt}_i + \beta_2\,\text{hp}_i + \beta_3\,\text{cyl}_i + \varepsilon_i
$$

```{python}
#| label: mlr-model

model_mlr = smf.ols("mpg ~ wt + hp + cyl", data=mtcars).fit()
print(model_mlr.summary())
```

## Coefficient Plot

```{python}
#| label: coef-plot
#| fig-cap: "Coefficient plot with 95% confidence intervals"

coefs = model_mlr.params.drop("Intercept")
conf  = model_mlr.conf_int().drop("Intercept")

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 3))
ax.errorbar(
    coefs, coefs.index,
    xerr=[coefs - conf[0], conf[1] - coefs],
    fmt="o", color="#4C72B0", capsize=5, linewidth=1.5
)
ax.axvline(0, linestyle="--", color="gray", linewidth=1)
ax.set_xlabel("Coefficient Estimate")
ax.set_title("Multiple Regression Coefficients (95% CI)")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
```

