# Interaction Terms {#sec-interaction}

Does the effect of weight on mpg differ by transmission type (`am`: 0 = automatic, 1 = manual)?

```{python}
#| label: interaction-model

model_int = smf.ols("mpg ~ wt * am", data=mtcars).fit()
print(model_int.summary())
```

```{python}
#| label: interaction-plot
#| fig-cap: "Interaction: effect of weight differs by transmission type"

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
colors = {0: "#4C72B0", 1: "#DD4444"}
labels = {0: "Automatic", 1: "Manual"}

for am_val, grp in mtcars.groupby("am"):
    ax.scatter(grp["wt"], grp["mpg"],
               color=colors[am_val], label=labels[am_val],
               alpha=0.8, edgecolors="white", s=70)
    x_r = np.linspace(grp["wt"].min(), grp["wt"].max(), 100)
    b0  = model_int.params["Intercept"]
    b1  = model_int.params["wt"]
    b2  = model_int.params["am"]
    b3  = model_int.params["wt:am"]
    y_r = b0 + b1*x_r + b2*am_val + b3*x_r*am_val
    ax.plot(x_r, y_r, color=colors[am_val], linewidth=2)

ax.set_xlabel("Weight (1000 lbs)")
ax.set_ylabel("Miles per Gallon")
ax.set_title("mpg ~ wt × Transmission Type")
ax.legend()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
```

