# Model Comparison {#sec-compare}

```{python}
#| label: model-compare

summary_tbl = pd.DataFrame({
    "Model":   ["SLR (wt)", "MLR (wt+hp+cyl)", "Interaction (wt×am)"],
    "R²":      [model_slr.rsquared, model_mlr.rsquared, model_int.rsquared],
    "Adj R²":  [model_slr.rsquared_adj, model_mlr.rsquared_adj, model_int.rsquared_adj],
    "AIC":     [model_slr.aic, model_mlr.aic, model_int.aic],
    "BIC":     [model_slr.bic, model_mlr.bic, model_int.bic],
}).round(3)

summary_tbl
```

> **Lower AIC/BIC** = better model fit penalised for complexity. **Higher Adj R²** = more variance explained without overfitting.

