# Summary

| Concept | Key Takeaway |
|---------|-------------|
| **OLS assumptions** | Linearity, independence, homoscedasticity, normality of errors |
| **`smf.ols()`** | R-style formula interface — readable and flexible |
| **`.summary()`** | Coefficients, SE, t-stats, p-values, R², F-stat in one table |
| **Diagnostics** | Always check residual plots and VIF before trusting inference |
| **Logistic regression** | Use `smf.logit()` for binary outcomes; interpret via odds ratios |

